<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Snorfen on 05-02-2001 06:17 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">hehe i agree if you can do some mana free damage why not dish it out?

In wackening lands i let my chante friend haste me, Strength buffed to 255 (with yaulp and high shammy STR) I did quite some damage in those long fights and all manafree... with Clarity 2 on me I was able to mostly crush and heal without sitting on my bum much.

Of course, If I do the right math, 2 landed reckonings would have done 1.2k damage and i could have med the mana back while mob gets beaten down... but, there are quite some mobs out there that have very high up to 100% magic resistance and doing some damage at start of fight when im still full mana is smart in my opinion.

I also have used to be the puller in most exp groups in Dreadlands, yes the cleric PULLING, this with Clarity caused me to stack the mobs right next to the group and the tanks only had just beaten down the first when I said: "one parked for bad days behind you" and already ran off for the next... This way we got like 8 to 15 mobs CONSTANTLY pulling, no downtime at all before I said: "ok need to med a bit, let the tank pull"

most people where just stunned at how fast exp and mobs where coming in and I still recieve shouts like "hey battlecleri howdy?" and what else could a dwarfen cleric want?

keep your style its a good one.

snorfen
